article.description: Tavon Blackmon scored 20 points, Cedric Kuakumensah had 15 points, 12 rebounds and four blocks, and Brown beat Bethune-Cookman 81-73 on Monday night.
article.headline: Kuakumensah's double-double leads Brown past Bethune-Cookman
article.linkText: Kuakumensah's double-double leads Brown past Bethune-Cookman
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Tavon Blackmon scored 20 points, Cedric Kuakumensah had 15 points, 12 rebounds and four blocks, and Brown beat Bethune-Cookman 81-73 on Monday night. Kuakumensah, who became the all-time blocks leader in Ivy League history earlier this month, posted his sixth double-double of the season. JR Hobbie made four 3-pointers and scored 13 points for Brown (4-7), which had not played at home since Dec. 2. Brown held a 36-29 lead at halftime behind Kuakumensah's 10 points and six rebounds. The Bears made 58 percent of their shots (14 of 24), but Diamante Lewis kept Bethune-Cookman close with 16 points. Brown opened the second half on a 12-1 run, with 3-pointers by Blackmon and Hobbie, to extend its lead to 48-30. Randy Holmes' 3-point play at the 16:38 mark was Bethune-Cookman's first made field goal after halftime. Jordan Potts and Lewis each scored 24 points for Bethune-Cookman (4-9).
